8
00:00:46,150 --> 00:00:48,950
 Is this your birth father's money? 

9
00:00:48,950 --> 00:00:50,850
 Gosh, no way! 

10
00:00:50,850 --> 00:00:52,940
 Where did you get this much money, then? 

11
00:00:52,940 --> 00:00:54,740
 I washed dishes and served tables. 

12
00:00:54,740 --> 00:00:57,800
 I caught a customer's eye and did some modeling, too. 

13
00:00:57,800 --> 00:01:00,810
 I worked really hard to pay you back... 

14
00:01:00,810 --> 00:01:02,260
 I worked hard. 

15
00:01:02,260 --> 00:01:05,120
 Did someone tell you to pay me back? 

16
00:01:05,120 --> 00:01:07,310
 Still, you raised me for ten years– 

17
00:01:07,310 --> 00:01:10,440
 What parent doesn't? It comes naturally! 

18
00:01:10,440 --> 00:01:13,640
 Is it because I'm not your real father? 

19
00:01:14,530 --> 00:01:16,110
 Leave. 

20
00:01:18,550 --> 00:01:20,770
 The reason Mr. Yoon got angry 

21
00:01:20,770 --> 00:01:25,070
 is because of his guilty conscience. Since you're not his birth dad. 

22
00:01:25,070 --> 00:01:27,580
 My handsome son. 

23
00:01:28,710 --> 00:01:30,970
   
   

24
00:01:30,970 --> 00:01:34,130
 Everyone, the model is here! 

25
00:01:36,050 --> 00:01:39,240
 It took me ten years to tell you that I like you. 

26
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:40,570
 Give me a chance. 

27
00:01:40,570 --> 00:01:44,500
 Give me a chance because Yoon Joo Won is my entire world. 

28
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:46,360
 I don't want things to become awkward between us. 

29
00:01:46,360 --> 00:01:50,390
 So I'm not going to give you the chance you asked for. 

30
00:01:50,390 --> 00:01:53,290
 - Yoon Joo Won. 
 - Kim San Ha is Yoon Joo Won's oppa. 

31
00:01:53,290 --> 00:01:55,880
 We can't become anything else. 

32
00:01:55,880 --> 00:01:57,420
 Even after this, 

33
00:01:58,420 --> 00:02:01,410
 we can't become anything else? 

34
00:02:03,190 --> 00:02:06,270
 I gave this a lot of thought. 

35
00:02:06,270 --> 00:02:10,670
 But I just can't forget your face that day. 

36
00:02:10,670 --> 00:02:13,030
 So I told her you're back here. 

37
00:02:13,030 --> 00:02:17,030
 It's up to you if you want to go see her or not. 

38
00:02:19,130 --> 00:02:21,330
 Is something wrong? 

39
00:02:21,330 --> 00:02:23,360
 - I saw Mom. 
 - Where? 

40
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:27,990
 Auntie told me she opened a hair salon in Busan. 

41
00:02:27,990 --> 00:02:31,330
 And? What did she say when she met you? 

42
00:02:31,330 --> 00:02:33,390
 I didn't meet her. 

43
00:02:33,390 --> 00:02:35,840
 I only saw her from afar. 

44
00:02:36,760 --> 00:02:38,150
 Did you find it? 

45
00:02:38,150 --> 00:02:42,210
 Yeah, the address was in a text from Auntie. 

46
00:02:57,110 --> 00:03:00,710
 So, does Hae Joon... 

47
00:03:02,670 --> 00:03:05,330
 Does Hae Joon also know that I'm here? 

48
00:03:07,070 --> 00:03:08,750
 He doesn't. 

49
00:03:17,550 --> 00:03:21,080
 Is it okay as long as you feel at ease? 

50
00:03:21,080 --> 00:03:22,900
 What about Kang Hae Joon? 

51
00:03:22,900 --> 00:03:28,000
 Kang Hae Joon lived his entire life in the dark, believing he was just baggage. 

52
00:03:31,970 --> 00:03:34,490
 Ever since you cut him off, 

53
00:03:34,490 --> 00:03:37,370
 he thought he was dead weight to you. 

54
00:03:38,540 --> 00:03:42,300
 People kept saying my dad took in a charity case! 

55
00:03:42,300 --> 00:03:46,500
 So he has thought of himself as an outsider for his entire life! 

56
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:48,590
 Do you even know? 

57
00:04:04,230 --> 00:04:05,940
 Gosh, what are you doing, Seo Hyeon? 

58
00:04:05,940 --> 00:04:09,560
 I just want him to... 

59
00:04:13,310 --> 00:04:16,860
 live an ordinary life. 

60
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:23,500
I already feel bad that he grew up with people pointing fingers and saying he was fatherless.

61
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:25,540
But now...

62
00:04:25,540 --> 00:04:28,520
his mom is a murderer, too.

63
00:04:29,420 --> 00:04:34,910
Right now, Jeong Jae and you guys are his family.

64
00:04:36,050 --> 00:04:39,950
My Hae Joon can continue to live an ordinary life.

65
00:04:39,950 --> 00:04:45,440
How can I become an obstacle to Hae Joon after all this time?

66
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:49,460
 I wouldn't be like this if it weren't for you. 

67
00:04:49,460 --> 00:04:52,750
 You made my life like this! 

68
00:04:59,880 --> 00:05:02,430
It's because of Kang Hae Joon.

69
00:05:15,380 --> 00:05:18,290
It is thanks to Kang Hae Joon

70
00:05:18,290 --> 00:05:22,490
that we are able to live happily like this.

71
00:05:27,260 --> 00:05:31,160
Because Kang Hae Joon is my dad's son,

72
00:05:31,960 --> 00:05:34,780
Kim San Ha's brother,

73
00:05:36,180 --> 00:05:38,610
and my oppa.

74
00:05:39,410 --> 00:05:44,210
Because Kang Hae Joon is there to smile for us during tough times

75
00:05:44,960 --> 00:05:48,720
and the first to cry when we are sad.

76
00:05:50,590 --> 00:05:53,990
That's why we can live happily like this.

77
00:05:59,080 --> 00:06:01,400
That same Kang Hae Joon...

78
00:06:08,180 --> 00:06:10,590
is waiting for you, Ahjumma.

79
00:06:12,610 --> 00:06:16,820
He wants to smile and cry with you.

80
00:06:17,460 --> 00:06:20,250
He wants to live ordinarily like that.

81
00:06:21,860 --> 00:06:24,450
He continues to wait for you.

82
00:06:49,750 --> 00:06:52,630
 Where are you? Are you at the hospital? 

83
00:06:52,630 --> 00:06:56,300
 Hurry home! Or call me when you see this. 

84
00:07:03,460 --> 00:07:05,170
   

85
00:07:06,470 --> 00:07:09,340
What's wrong with everyone?

86
00:07:09,340 --> 00:07:10,480
What do you mean?

87
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:12,860
They don't talk about their own pain,

88
00:07:12,860 --> 00:07:15,340
thinking, "I'm the only one who has to suffer."

89
00:07:15,340 --> 00:07:17,120
You were like that, too.

90
00:07:17,120 --> 00:07:19,350
- Was I? 
 - Don't you remember?

91
00:07:19,350 --> 00:07:23,110
You were hurt by the words, "For someone without a mom."

92
00:07:23,110 --> 00:07:27,580
But you didn't tell Hae Joon or me knowing we'd get upset.

93
00:07:27,580 --> 00:07:30,110
That was ages ago.

94
00:07:30,810 --> 00:07:34,040
Hae Joon and Ahjumma will be okay.

95
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:35,800
Exactly.

96
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:38,970
Why don't they talk it out before they feel hurt?

97
00:07:38,970 --> 00:07:42,830
They'll understand and forgive in the end, anyway.

98
00:07:42,830 --> 00:07:46,360
I'm just frustrated. Really frustrated.

99
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:49,160
Not everything is understandable.

100
00:07:54,400 --> 00:07:56,690
You're okay, right?

101
00:07:58,580 --> 00:08:02,270
- By chance– 
 - So did you live happily, thanks to Hae Joon?

102
00:08:02,270 --> 00:08:03,780
What?

103
00:08:03,780 --> 00:08:07,490
Did you live happily, thanks to Hae Joon and not me?

104
00:08:08,860 --> 00:08:10,430
No.

105
00:08:10,430 --> 00:08:14,050
Did I say that? When did I say that?

106
00:08:14,050 --> 00:08:16,080
I don't know.

107
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:19,080
Are you jealous of Hae Joon in the midst of this?

108
00:08:38,460 --> 00:08:41,870
Mom, can we sleep here tonight?

109
00:08:41,870 --> 00:08:45,090
Why sleep here when we have a perfectly nice hotel?

110
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:51,140
But Mom, it looks like Oppa lives here.

111
00:08:51,140 --> 00:08:53,390
He should live properly, even if it's just for one month.

112
00:08:53,390 --> 00:08:56,590
Anything less than this will be uncomfortable.

113
00:08:56,590 --> 00:08:59,160
Is Kim San Ha only staying for a month?

114
00:08:59,160 --> 00:09:02,680
I wish you wouldn't butt into our family conversation.

115
00:09:03,910 --> 00:09:05,580
All right.

116
00:09:05,580 --> 00:09:08,050
Please close the door on your way out.

117
00:09:13,840 --> 00:09:18,990
But I'm not exactly a total stranger when it comes to Kim San Ha.

118
00:09:30,770 --> 00:09:32,200
 - The call is not going through...  
 - My goodness.

119
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:34,980
What's he doing that he can't answer the phone?

120
00:10:02,540 --> 00:10:05,430
- Where are you two coming from? 
 - What?

121
00:10:05,430 --> 00:10:10,340
Well, we are coming back from...

122
00:10:10,340 --> 00:10:13,100
Why are you standing out here?

123
00:10:13,100 --> 00:10:16,470
Oh, right! Do you know how many times I called you?

124
00:10:16,470 --> 00:10:18,130
Me?

125
00:10:20,080 --> 00:10:21,910
Your mom is here.

126
00:10:28,020 --> 00:10:30,710
Go home. I'll call you later.

127
00:10:30,710 --> 00:10:32,910
No, you come inside, too.

128
00:10:32,910 --> 00:10:34,450
I'm a little scared.

129
00:10:34,450 --> 00:10:37,080
Then you can stay at Joo Won's for a bit.

130
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:39,920
No, I want to come, too.

131
00:10:39,920 --> 00:10:42,190
Go home.

132
00:10:42,190 --> 00:10:43,960
Take her home.

133
00:10:49,970 --> 00:10:51,500
Let's go inside.

134
00:10:55,620 --> 00:10:57,650
Oppa!

135
00:10:58,990 --> 00:11:00,930
What is this?

136
00:11:00,930 --> 00:11:02,150
What brings you here?

137
00:11:02,150 --> 00:11:04,560
Mom wanted to see the Busan beach.

138
00:11:04,560 --> 00:11:07,330
We came to see you while we were here.

139
00:11:07,330 --> 00:11:09,720
- Where is Mom? 
 - In your room.

140
00:11:09,720 --> 00:11:11,330
All right.

141
00:11:17,370 --> 00:11:19,700
 I wouldn't be like this if it weren't for you. 

142
00:11:19,700 --> 00:11:21,380
 Do you think I'm acting like this because I'm drunk? 

143
00:11:21,380 --> 00:11:24,390
 Because I can't walk? 

144
00:11:25,220 --> 00:11:27,030
 It's all your fault. 

145
00:11:27,030 --> 00:11:29,360
 You made my life like this! 

146
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:32,690
 You made my life like this! 

147
00:11:37,910 --> 00:11:40,580
You even changed the hospital, didn't you?

148
00:11:41,560 --> 00:11:43,650
I told you I came back permanently.

149
00:11:43,650 --> 00:11:45,930
And I said you can't.

150
00:11:57,800 --> 00:12:00,740
- Mom– 
 - So, will you be selfish until the end

151
00:12:00,740 --> 00:12:03,380
and do what you want?

152
00:12:05,560 --> 00:12:08,380
Must you see me die?

153
00:12:13,990 --> 00:12:15,880
You won't die.

154
00:12:19,050 --> 00:12:23,420
You'll be all right, Mom.

155
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:29,650
Are you saying you don't care if I die?

156
00:12:29,650 --> 00:12:32,060
How could you treat me like this?

157
00:12:32,060 --> 00:12:35,300
I'm saying you won't blink an eye even if I die!

158
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:44,910
I was scared something would happen to you, too.

159
00:12:44,910 --> 00:12:49,110
That I would lose you like we lost So Jeong.

160
00:12:49,110 --> 00:12:53,650
I was scared every single day for the last ten years.

161
00:12:53,650 --> 00:12:56,180
But I was the only one.

162
00:13:00,500 --> 00:13:02,140
 Only me. 

163
00:13:03,640 --> 00:13:05,070
 You ruined my life! 

164
00:13:05,070 --> 00:13:09,190
 I was the only one who thought I couldn't live without you, Mom. 

165
00:13:09,190 --> 00:13:10,720
 Only me. 

166
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:16,010
You never cried...

167
00:13:16,830 --> 00:13:19,070
for your children.

168
00:13:19,070 --> 00:13:21,410
How dare you spew nonsense?

169
00:13:21,410 --> 00:13:23,170
What do you know?

170
00:13:23,170 --> 00:13:26,480
You don't know how much I cried for So Jeong!

171
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:30,290
Did you really cry for So Jeong?

172
00:13:30,290 --> 00:13:32,460
Mom!

173
00:13:32,460 --> 00:13:33,830
Oppa, what's wrong?

174
00:13:33,830 --> 00:13:36,380
Tell her you're sorry.

175
00:13:40,710 --> 00:13:43,440
Take So Hui and go back to Seoul.

176
00:13:45,270 --> 00:13:47,170
I'm not going.

177
00:13:54,580 --> 00:14:01,500
♫  Back then, we were too young to know our hearts were racing  ♫

178
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:11,500
♫  We just argued and delayed things without knowing why  ♫

179
00:14:14,580 --> 00:14:20,740
♫  Maybe we didn’t understand the meaning of love  ♫

180
00:14:20,740 --> 00:14:24,400
♫  We just couldn’t say it  ♫

181
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:30,440
♫  Each day, like that  ♫

182
00:14:30,440 --> 00:14:36,700
♫  Maybe we didn’t understand the meaning of goodbye either  ♫

183
00:14:36,700 --> 00:14:40,300
♫  We just believed  ♫

184
00:14:40,300 --> 00:14:43,680
♫  we didn't want to let go of each other  ♫

185
00:14:43,680 --> 00:14:47,140
Please. Please...

186
00:14:47,140 --> 00:14:55,050
♫  While carrying the warmth of our memories in our hearts  ♫

187
00:15:22,470 --> 00:15:25,700
   

188
00:15:27,330 --> 00:15:29,240
Hey, Daughter.

189
00:15:31,100 --> 00:15:32,990
Of course.

190
00:15:35,690 --> 00:15:41,440
Thanks to someone's wise daughter's words, there was nothing left for me to say.

191
00:15:42,170 --> 00:15:44,200
Ahjumma will get in touch in no time.

192
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:46,670
 You have to let me know if she does, okay? 

193
00:15:46,670 --> 00:15:48,470
 Kang Hae Joon is coming. I'll call you later. 

194
00:15:48,470 --> 00:15:50,120
Okay.

195
00:15:56,630 --> 00:15:59,210
When did you come?

196
00:15:59,210 --> 00:16:02,460
What Ahjumma?

197
00:16:04,570 --> 00:16:09,390
You still have a long way to go until you need hearing aids, Madam.

198
00:16:09,390 --> 00:16:10,880
You have super hearing.

199
00:16:10,880 --> 00:16:12,670
Why are you changing the subject?

200
00:16:12,670 --> 00:16:14,900
What Ahjumma?

201
00:16:14,900 --> 00:16:19,490
I wonder how much lunch traffic we will get today.

202
00:16:19,490 --> 00:16:21,810
The weather is so nice.

203
00:16:23,530 --> 00:16:25,990
Something is fishy.

204
00:16:25,990 --> 00:16:27,990
I'm sure of it.

205
00:16:29,440 --> 00:16:32,190
Did he get a girlfriend?

206
00:16:32,190 --> 00:16:36,140
Mr. Yoon, did you get a girlfriend?

207
00:16:37,690 --> 00:16:39,340
Still no word from Kim San Ha?

208
00:16:39,340 --> 00:16:40,820
He must've been at the hospital all night.

209
00:16:40,820 --> 00:16:44,880
I asked Joon Ho, and he said Oppa was in the ER and just fell asleep.

210
00:16:50,140 --> 00:16:52,340
Hey, I mean, listen.

211
00:16:52,340 --> 00:16:55,810
Is it that hard to tell us he's going to the hospital?

212
00:16:55,810 --> 00:16:57,270
Even Ahjumma and the little girl.

213
00:16:57,270 --> 00:17:00,980
I was shocked to discover they all disappeared without a trace.

214
00:17:03,440 --> 00:17:05,140
Anyway,

215
00:17:06,840 --> 00:17:08,150
where did she go?

216
00:17:08,150 --> 00:17:09,980
Who? Dal?

217
00:17:09,980 --> 00:17:12,130
Did she leave early this morning?

218
00:17:14,810 --> 00:17:17,190
Did she not come home?

219
00:17:17,940 --> 00:17:19,350
What if she didn't?

220
00:17:19,350 --> 00:17:23,490
What's wrong with a single, 29-year-old woman staying out?

221
00:17:23,490 --> 00:17:24,910
It's a scary world these days.

222
00:17:24,910 --> 00:17:28,290
How could she stay out all night? She has no fear.

223
00:17:29,650 --> 00:17:33,190
Does that mean she already found a boyfriend?

224
00:17:33,190 --> 00:17:36,590
Wow, she just asked me to be her fake partner the other day.

225
00:17:36,590 --> 00:17:38,410
Who is it?

226
00:17:39,190 --> 00:17:43,000
Dal went home yesterday because it was her mom's birthday.

227
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:45,650
Why did you lie?

228
00:17:45,650 --> 00:17:48,100
What's with the overreaction?

229
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:52,760
Why do you care whether Dal stays out or finds a boyfriend?

230
00:17:52,760 --> 00:17:55,160
You know, my sister's friend is my sister.

231
00:17:55,160 --> 00:17:57,370
She's like you to me.

232
00:17:57,370 --> 00:18:01,210
I'm telling you just in case, but I don't need that kind of attention from you.

233
00:18:02,310 --> 00:18:04,050
This won't do.

234
00:18:04,050 --> 00:18:07,030
Pack Kim San Ha's belongings. I'll stop by the hospital.

235
00:18:07,030 --> 00:18:08,420
You can go to work. I'll go.

236
00:18:08,420 --> 00:18:11,390
- I'll go. 
 - There's no need. I'll go.

237
00:18:11,390 --> 00:18:13,920
I said I'll go!

238
00:18:18,540 --> 00:18:20,320
There is something, isn't there?

239
00:18:20,320 --> 00:18:23,820
- What? 
 - Something you're not telling me.

240
00:18:26,880 --> 00:18:28,950
You two...

241
00:18:28,950 --> 00:18:30,830
Us two, what?

242
00:18:35,550 --> 00:18:38,910
You got your wrist treated at the hospital last time.

243
00:18:38,910 --> 00:18:40,800
Are you in pain again?

244
00:18:42,160 --> 00:18:46,380
Do you want to see how strong my fist and wrist are?

245
00:18:46,380 --> 00:18:48,250
You have to tell me if it hurts, okay?

246
00:18:48,250 --> 00:18:50,520
I'll pack Kim San Ha's stuff.

247
00:18:54,740 --> 00:18:58,440
He consistently can't read the room.

248
00:19:05,060 --> 00:19:07,350
What is he hiding here?

249
00:19:08,850 --> 00:19:12,200
   

250
00:19:32,050 --> 00:19:33,430
 Are you awake? 

251
00:19:33,430 --> 00:19:36,550
 I'm on my way to the hospital. 

252
00:19:59,330 --> 00:20:05,200
♫  Why am I like this?  ♫

253
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:13,360
♫  Why am I always so excited like it's the first time?  ♫

254
00:20:13,360 --> 00:20:18,240
♫  Even in bright daylight, the stars shine  ♫

255
00:20:18,240 --> 00:20:20,380
Did you eat?

256
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:23,360
That's a lie.

257
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:28,220
I'll tell Dad that Kim San Ha skips his breakfast.

258
00:20:28,960 --> 00:20:32,310
I'll keep my mouth shut if you buy me something tasty.

259
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:39,060
Let's go.

260
00:20:48,050 --> 00:20:51,240
- Dad! 
 - Hey, Son. You're here.

261
00:20:53,620 --> 00:20:56,430
I'll get that.

262
00:21:01,090 --> 00:21:02,760
Wow...

263
00:21:02,760 --> 00:21:06,130
You must be the famous model son.

