366
00:27:10,790 --> 00:27:12,860
Poor woman. Goodness.

367
00:27:12,860 --> 00:27:16,060
Yes, you're right.

368
00:27:16,060 --> 00:27:18,200
I misspoke.

369
00:27:18,850 --> 00:27:21,540
How did it go with Hae Joon's mom?

370
00:27:23,380 --> 00:27:25,190
I feel sorry for her.

371
00:27:25,190 --> 00:27:27,570
She got on her knees and cried yesterday.

372
00:27:27,570 --> 00:27:29,970
I thought about how sad her life is.

373
00:27:29,970 --> 00:27:34,020
It made me wonder how she lasted 20 years without Hae Joon.

374
00:27:35,820 --> 00:27:39,610
It would've been great if you started living together after the blind date.

375
00:27:42,120 --> 00:27:46,280
Didn't you have feelings for Hae Joon's mom?

376
00:27:46,280 --> 00:27:49,600
Listen to this guy. Who had what?

377
00:27:49,600 --> 00:27:52,230
That's what I thought all this time.

378
00:27:52,230 --> 00:27:56,300
Isn't that why you took in Hae Joon without a second thought?

379
00:27:56,300 --> 00:27:58,200
Goodness.

380
00:27:58,200 --> 00:28:00,450
Don't say that carelessly in front of the children.

381
00:28:00,450 --> 00:28:02,870
What absolute nonsense.

382
00:28:02,870 --> 00:28:05,910
Finish eating and go to San Ha.

383
00:28:08,870 --> 00:28:12,240
If it's not true, just say so. Why get angry?

384
00:28:12,240 --> 00:28:14,920
That's funny. My goodness.

385
00:28:19,610 --> 00:28:21,350
So Hui.

386
00:28:24,210 --> 00:28:26,050
Oppa.

387
00:28:29,490 --> 00:28:31,770
What brings you all the way here alone?

388
00:28:31,770 --> 00:28:33,340
Sit down.

389
00:28:34,660 --> 00:28:35,770
Where's Mom?

390
00:28:35,770 --> 00:28:38,400
Mom is still at the hotel in Busan.

391
00:28:39,120 --> 00:28:41,330
She thinks I'm back in Seoul.

392
00:28:41,330 --> 00:28:45,360
She said she'd stay one more day and told me to return first.

393
00:28:47,050 --> 00:28:48,290
By yourself?

394
00:28:48,290 --> 00:28:51,560
Mom isn't answering her phone right now.

395
00:28:58,020 --> 00:29:01,170
Don't worry. You know she gets like this sometimes.

396
00:29:01,170 --> 00:29:03,810
It's nothing to worry about,

397
00:29:03,810 --> 00:29:08,280
so if you return to Seoul, she'll call you in no time.

398
00:29:08,280 --> 00:29:11,600
Mom cried so much at the hotel yesterday.

399
00:29:15,180 --> 00:29:21,540
Oppa, can't I just live with you until I graduate high school?

400
00:29:24,670 --> 00:29:29,020
Mom is better off without me.

401
00:29:29,020 --> 00:29:31,060
That's not true.

402
00:29:31,060 --> 00:29:36,450
Mom was sensitive at times, but that's because she was in pain.

403
00:29:36,450 --> 00:29:40,320
But she was able to rehabilitate

404
00:29:40,320 --> 00:29:43,390
because you and I were by her side.

405
00:29:44,190 --> 00:29:46,380
 Psychogenic? 

406
00:29:46,380 --> 00:29:49,520
 You can see for yourself, but there's no bone, muscle, or nerve damage. 

407
00:29:49,520 --> 00:29:52,580
 With so much effort in rehab, and yet there's no progress? 

408
00:29:52,580 --> 00:29:54,480
 It could be psychogenic. 

409
00:29:54,480 --> 00:29:57,350
 Consider transferring her to psychiatry. 

410
00:30:00,740 --> 00:30:07,420
Mom has a harder time when I'm around.

411
00:30:08,410 --> 00:30:11,100
 To Mom, I'm... 

412
00:30:11,100 --> 00:30:14,570
 Mom! Mom! 

413
00:30:14,570 --> 00:30:17,210
 I'm like the scar on her leg. 

414
00:30:18,490 --> 00:30:20,860
 If her scar disappeared... 

415
00:30:22,640 --> 00:30:26,010
all her painful memories would disappear, too.

416
00:30:26,940 --> 00:30:29,580
But she can still see it.

417
00:30:29,580 --> 00:30:34,940
And every time she sees it, she feels awful.

418
00:30:36,300 --> 00:30:39,000
- Oppa. 
 - That's why...

419
00:30:40,060 --> 00:30:41,940
Mom is better off...

420
00:30:43,130 --> 00:30:45,400
without me there.

421
00:30:49,590 --> 00:30:54,140
You know how much Mom loves you, right?

422
00:30:56,630 --> 00:31:01,390
Mom will get better because of you.

423
00:31:09,970 --> 00:31:12,130
I'm here.

424
00:31:12,130 --> 00:31:13,730
Hey.

425
00:31:19,490 --> 00:31:22,160
Kang Hae Joon isn't coming today.

426
00:31:22,900 --> 00:31:26,480
Give me a cupcake. The first one.

427
00:31:26,480 --> 00:31:28,380
- Me, too. 
 - Two?

428
00:31:28,380 --> 00:31:29,920
Yes.

429
00:31:36,260 --> 00:31:39,650
Did you know Hae Joon's rumors are rampant at the nurses' station?

430
00:31:39,650 --> 00:31:43,020
